				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Small rant I suppose.
<br />

<br />
I did a who all /enchanter 20 50 so I would capture the number of enchanters this past week. Averaged around 32 to 34 prime time.
<br />
While most other types ranged in the 100+ region.
<br />

<br />
Gave up playing the enchanter, spent two weeks with only getting one group worth mentioning. I play about 3 hours at a time and have spent at least 9 of those days LFG for one and one half hours or more. I shout, ooc, explain mez ability, and flag myself lfg and try to start groups which inevitably fails due to no healer being available.
<br />

<br />
Am I missing something here? I have tried commonlands, WC, FG and Nek with no success.
<br />

<br />
I just don't believe chanters are needed as most 4 spawn groups can be taken with a single healer, or 4 spawn yellow / orange, or double up arrow with a secondary healer, no need for mez. I was even asked while in a group what I was doing since they thought I was HIGH dps like a wizard, I explained the dots and CC, group broke up shortly thereafter.
<br />

<br />
So much for being able to substitute any mage class for any other mage class, looks like it's back to needing Healer, MT, DPS.
<br />

<br />
Ah well, playing an assassin now in a dedicated group with some RL friends, nothing is better than having a dedicated group for consistent xp. And it's amazing in 22 lvls we have never needed an enchanter although I do enjoy when they are in the group.
<br />

<br />
Just confused I guess and trying to figure out if I am missing something.
<br />

<br />
G.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
