This states exactly how I feel. In EQ1 I felt I was really making a difference to the group, through buffs and CC (slowing was the shaman's province, woe betide me if I tried <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /> ) and all the other myriad things I could do. I loved being needed and making the difference to the group... a small group of us would try stuff that nobody dared, and between us we had enough unique skills that we achieved amazing things.
<br />

<br />
