				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /> I think you misread me, I said:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I'm <span style="font-weight: bold">not</span> one to spam group chat with "stunning %T, please oooh and ahhh now"</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Really I think just mentioning the one time when you don't do your job correctly will make them take notice how important you are when you do. This can get you into trouble though if you're with jerks who are just looking for an excuse to comment on your usefulness. As someone already mentioned, there is a fine line between being critical for a groups success and being held responsible for each of its failures.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
