			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Devil's advocate for a moment....
<br />
This is not EQ1. I know, I know - but really. This is NOT EQ1. I've been saying this since release, and honestly thought I believed it, but it only really hit me at gut level recently. 
<br />

<br />
CC is just not nearly as required here. There are so many alternatives, groups have a LOT of different ways to do just fine thankyouverymuch with no chanter. My regular group is utterly used to a chanter being a group enhancer, but these same people really don't need me now. They still WANT me there, sure, because I'm a pal, but the CC aspect is now relegated to emergency only. ONLY. Like, maybe once or twice a night. They just don't need the mobs queued up any more, and in fact they have so many AEs between them that frankly, my mezzing just slows things down. And I'm not talking wizards here, but hmm.. guardian, assassin, zerker, brawler, cleric, couple druids, and shaman are the changing components of the team. ANY selection of those assuming it includes at least one tank and one healer can do just fine.
<br />

<br />
They're ambivalent about haste - it's quite nice, but some of them have proccing powers and haste makes the power on those go whoosh. They don't even notice the standard buffs <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /> I'm lagging behind their levels a little bit so it makes it a bit harder for me to do DPS (a lot of stuff won't hit or stick). So mostly what I bring to the table is breeze - which the guardian loves, and the rest of them like if it's around, don't miss if it's not.
<br />

<br />
I spent a while feeling sorry for myself and thinking "Waah I've been gimped, this is not the class I thought it was" and then.. you know, this is NOT the class I thought it was, but it's still ok. There's a bunch of stuff I can (potentially, given sensible level ranges) do. It's not all about mez any more. BUT - and here's the big but - chanters are a luxury. They're not a necessity. It's been said elsewhere I know, but I'm not sure how well that's really sunk in. Nobody NEEDS chanters now. There's nowhere you can't go without a chanter. A chanter may save your ass from a horrible pull, but you know what - the guardian might save it too - or the brawler - or the assassin - or who knows (we're light on mages) maybe a wizard. 
<br />

<br />
I know in our guild quite a few folks have sort of relaxed into what they THINK their class does, based on years of experience of EQ1. It's no longer true, and they're not using their classes properly in most cases. Sure they're doing DPS or they're healing, but they sort of gloss over the extra, unfamiliar stuff (especially HOs). 
<br />

<br />
I'm sorry for the book! I sort of lost my way in there. Um. Oh yeah. I think maybe some of us are feeling disenchanted (heh) with the class because we feel like we're not fulfilling what we THOUGHT was our proper role. I feel much better now I've taken another look at coercer and thought of a whole truckload of tactics which don't involve stuns or mezzing, and tried to break my ingrained habits of play....  for those feeling disgruntled, that might work for you too.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal">Ilira [L65 Coercer] Cazic Thule[retired]
<br />
Ilira [L29 Coercer] Runnyeye </span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
