				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I kind of enjoy not having to mez that much anymore.  
<br />

<br />
Sure, it was fun, but in eq1 if you got a resist it took a lot of luck to survive it, even with all the AA under the sun, and good gear. <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="Sad" border="0" />
<br />
At least in the current exp mobs hitting for 900 situation.
<br />

<br />
Now I view myself more in group support, rather than group miracle worker.
<br />

<br />
In eq2 I view myself as a mob nerf bat. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Mob : RAR
<br />
Tank : eek
<br />
Thandor hits the mob with his nerf bat of spells (+5)
<br />
Mob : eek
<br />
Tank : RAR!
<br />

<br />

<br />
Hehe <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
We arent essential, but hey.  I *hated* being spammed with group requests, which when refused turn into buff begging.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
